Now how many drivers drive without a seat belt, run red lights, etc. Also, how many people have access to cars vs access to skydiving? And then in cars, how many people have access TO THEIR OWN car vs how many people can skydive on their own? You can get a license and car with almost little effort in the US vs skydiving which requires a ton of training - and rightfully so.

If we made people train to drive like we do skydiving or scuba or anything else like that, you'd see much lower numbers.
